ENTRY            40845   20251006   20260319   20260319       4226
SUBENT        40845001   20251006   20260319   20260319       4226
BIB                 14         34
TITLE       Angular anisotropy of inelastic neutron scattering
            on Se nuclei, and the role of the direct mechanisms
            at En = 1 MeV
AUTHOR     (E.S.Konobeevskii,Yu.G.Kudenko,M.V.Mordovskoi,
           V.I.Popov,V.M.Skorkin)
REFERENCE  (J,BAS,48,(2),169,1984) Engl.transl.of IZV,48,389,1984
           (J,IZV,48,389,1984)     Main reference . Issue 2 .
           ((S,INDC(CCP)-235,(3),157,1984)=
           (C,83KIEV,3,157,1983))
INSTITUTE  (4RUSJIA)
FACILITY   (VDG,4RUSJIA) EG-2.5 accelerator in pulse mode.
INC-SOURCE (P-T) Proton beam of 2 MeV energy,
           3 nsec pulse duration,
           3-4 muA current on solid tritium target of 60 keV
           thickness.
SAMPLE      Metallic selenium,  particular isotope enrichment
            is 92 - 99 percent,sample weight 50 - 100 gram
METHOD     (TOF) Flight base is 2. m
DETECTOR   (SCIN)  Stilbene crystal
MONITOR    (1-H-1(N,EL)1-H-1,,SIG)
MONIT-REF  (,A.Horsley,J,ND/A,2,243,1966) np scattering data used
           for normalization.
CORRECTION   On absorption and multiple scattering of neutrons,
             on angular resolution etc
ADD-RES    (POT) Potential parameters given in the 83KIEV,3,157
HISTORY    (19850325C)
           (19860117A) Several new Subentries introduced
           (20010319A) Date is Corrected. One Subent added
           (20010326U) Last checking has been done.
           (20180309A) M.M. Ref.BAS,48,(2),169,1984 was added.
           STATUS was added in data Subents.
           Monitor was corrected.
           (20251006A) Ref. S,INDC(CCP)-235 was added.
           STATUS was corrected for new rules.
ENDBIB              34
NOCOMMON             0          0
ENDSUBENT           37
